{"lemma":"رافِضَة","slug":"رافِضَة","root":"ر.ف.ض","root_slug":"ر-ف-ض","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ف-ض","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16146"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%90%D8%B6%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16146","headword_ar":"رَافِضَةٌ","root":"rfD","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A party of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawaAfiD","text_ar":"رَوَافِض"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) whence the rel. n. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAfiDaY~N","text_ar":"رَافِضَىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belonging to,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawaAfiD","text_ar":"رَوَافِض"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawaAfiDu","text_ar":"رَوَافِضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAfiDapN","text_ar":"رَافِضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An army,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a military force,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any army"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"military force,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which has deserted its leader:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"armies which have deserted their leader."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aAfiDapN","text_ar":"الرَّافِضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain sect of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyEap","text_ar":"شِيعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of ElKoofeh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) so called because they deserted Zeyd the son of 'Alee, (As, S, Mgh, Msb,) when he forbade them to speak against the Companions of the Prophet; (Mgh, Msb;) for they had promised allegiance to Zeyd the son of 'Alee (As, O, L, K) the son of El-Hoseyn the son of 'Alee the son of Aboo-Tálib, (As, O, L,) and then desired him to renounce the two elders, [Aboo-Bekr and 'Omar, (TK,)] and on his refusing to do so they deserted him: (As, O, L, K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^arofaADu","text_ar":"الاَرْفَاضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied to this sect, as though it were pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAfiDN","text_ar":"رَافِضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSoHaAbN","text_ar":"اَصْحَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHbN","text_ar":"صَاحبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~awaAfiDu","text_ar":"الرَّوَافِضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also; but not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~uf~aADu","text_ar":"الرُّفَّاضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and the rel. n. [which serves as a n. un.] is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAfiDaY~N","text_ar":"رَافِضَىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as above]. (K.) Afterwards, this appellation became applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"All persons transgressing in this way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all apostates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"schismatics,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speaking against the Companions of the Prophet."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibilN","text_ar":"اـِبِلٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAfiDpN","text_ar":"رَافِضةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafoDN","text_ar":"رَفْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["K","S","O","Msb","As","Mgh","L","TK","TA"]}]}}